Kill those canned dogs. Be careful not to get bitten. Canned dogs in a frenzy have significantly increased attack power. Rolling with space can avoid any form of damage.

Open your backpack and equip your sword. Hitting Tin Can Dog six times or more triggers its vulnerability state, causing a significant decrease in its attack power. Before that, be sure to avoid Tin Can Dog's attacks! 
After completion, enter the main town and find Nash to end the mission

Press [Esc] to open your talent tree interface, select the main branch to upgrade, choose to upgrade the War Stomp skill, and place the skill in the quick slot. By completing these steps, you can use the War Stomp skill in combat. Mastering this skill will make your battles much easier.
Follow the guide points to your homeland, use a hoe to till the cultivable land, and then sow the seeds on the tilled land.

Patience is key. Observe the style of the land and the condition of the crops. If the land is dry, it needs to be watered immediately. The number of times different crops need to be watered to mature varies. Remember, crops can wither and die if not watered for too long.

Follow the guide points to collect grass with a sickle, trees with an axe, and stones with a pickaxe. After completing these tasks, return to Silas and open the crafting interface. Select "Craft Gathering Essence" to begin crafting.
I have obtained five pieces of ordinary wood and five stones.

Farm for enough regular wood and gather enough fiber to unlock recipes by upgrading the left side nodes of the gathering talent tree. Then, craft an iron pickaxe. Combat may be necessary to protect yourself while gathering resources.
